snippet.textDisplay:
Watching this race I realised:
1. Even in 2016 TV cameras couldn't give a shit about Carlos, even when driving at a rate, where he could finish career best.
2. Seb is way better in wet conditions than any of the new fans want to give him credit for. He was 15th after all and fought back in this "shitbox of a car" as Niki Lauda would say.
3. 2016 was pretty boring for the vast majority of the season, but it had highlights, e.g. Spain, Brazil, Abu Dhabi. Still worse than every other season of the turbo hybrid era.
4. Esteban is going to give Daniel a hard time at Renault, when the 2020 season (or 2020/2021 to be more accurate) will start.
5. Wet conditions produce the most fun races to watch. Here is hope for Canada 2011, Germany 2019 or even older ones to be rewatchable, but I'm not sure, if Liberty Media can get the rights to those.
